stop

public void stop()
Stop the timed task. This takes the current system time and saves it. Calling stop on TimedTasks that have been stopped before has no effect. If the task was given a recordAt argument at construction time, it will be recorded there.

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Get a string representing this timed task. If the task has not been stopped yet, it will be stopped.

Overrides:
